The West African College of Surgeons has concluded plans to undertake free surgical operations for patients of hernia, breast lumps, thyroid (goitre), fibroid, cleft lip, cleft palate, cataract and glaucoma, in the Federal Capital Territory (FCT). A statement issued by the director of special duties, FCT Health and Human Services Secretariat (HHSS), Dr Matthew Ashikeni, which was made available to LEADERSHIP in Abuja yesterday, said that the free surgical outreach would be flagged-off by the FCT minister, Malam Muhammad Musa Bello on 9th February, 2020. The statement added that members of the college, who are mainly specialised surgeons, gynaecologist, ENT surgeons, Ophthalmologists and radiologists, would conduct the outreach from 9th-15th February, 2020 in eight general hospitals in the FCT, as part of its 60th annual conference to be held in the FCT, from 17-21, February, 2020. FCT general hospitals listed for the exercise, according to Ashikeni, include Bwari, Kubwa, Kuje, Kwali, Wuse, including the Federal Medical Centre (FMC) Jabi, Rachel Eye Hospital, Area 11, as well as the Garki Hospital. He added that other hospitals to be used outside the FCT are the General Hospital Lambata, in Niger State, General Hospital, Mararaba, Nasarawa State and Specialist Hospital, Lokoja in Kogi State. The statement, therefore directed all area council chairmen, where the exercise would be taking place to mobilise residents, especially those with any of the listed surgical conditions to the nearest participating health facility for free registration, which would commence on Monday, December 2, 2019 to February 8, 2020, in all the listed hospitals.